cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CE, cs.NI, cs.SY 

This paper discusses an experimental attack on a secure key exchange system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attack involves manipulating the attenuation of signals, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and communication engineering (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the use of noise in the key exchange system, which relates to network security (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
